quran[6]{c,v,t,f}:
  6,133,"And your Lord is Rich (Free of all needs), full of Mercy; if He wills, He can destroy you, and in your place make whom He wills as your successors, as He raised you from the seed of other people."
  6,134,"Surely, that which you are promised will verily come to pass, and you cannot escape (from the punishment of Allâh)."
  6,135,"Say (O Muhammad صلى الله عليه وسلم): "
  7,43,"And We shall remove from their breasts any (mutual) hatred or sense of injury (which they had, if at all, in the life of this world); rivers flowing under them, and they will say: "
  7,44,"And the dwellers of Paradise will call out to the dwellers of the Fire (saying): "
  7,45,"Those who hindered (men) from the Path of Allâh, and would seek to make it crooked, and they were disbelievers in the Hereafter."